<item>
            <title>[MATH-924] new multivariate vector optimizers cannot be used with large number of weights</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-924</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the Weigth class to pass a large number of weights to multivariate vector optimizers, an nxn full matrix is created (and copied) when a n elements vector is used. This exhausts memory when n is large.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens for example when using curve fitters (even simple curve fitters like polynomial ones for low degree) with large number of points. I encountered this with curve fitting on 41200 points, which created a matrix with 1.7 billion elements.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
