                            <comment id="13540582" author="luc" created="Fri, 28 Dec 2012 20:18:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in subversion repository as of r1426616.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13540730" author="erans" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2012 02:20:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Keeping the matrix concept, by representing uncorrelated observations with a diagonal weight matrix (instead of an array), allows to solve this issue with minimal changes to the code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The optimizer&apos;s API is untouched.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The possibility to have correlated observations is kept.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The attached patch contains a minimal &quot;DiagonalMatrix&quot; implementation, needing overview (ant unit tests).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13540904" author="erans" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2012 13:18:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changes committed in revision 1426758.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same problem would occur int the deprecated &quot;o.a.c.m.optimization&quot; package. The same changes must be ported there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13540906" author="erans" created="Sat, 29 Dec 2012 13:27:16 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The same changes must be ported there.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

